messages.message: Hi France! What are your plans in the early game? Would you be up for an FG to take out England? I think we could work together really well against him, and then you can go south with your fleets and I can go east with my armies.

Hi England! What are your plans in the early game? Would you be up for an alliance? I think that's the best way to go, as we can work together against France, and you can go south with your fleets and I can go east with my armies.
Hey Germany, good luck this game. Just wanted to establish early communication. Any interest in moving an army to Silesia to help me against Russia?
Hi Russia! I would be happy to let you into Sweden if you opened to take out Turkey, I'd like to be able to fight England.
Hey Germany! It's a tough sell for me to accept an offer like that from England when I haven't even heard from him yet.
As for the early game I'm interested in taking Belgium of course, but I would want to see something like Mun-tyr, Kie-den and Ber-kie this turn.

Hi Italy! I wanted to get in touch early on. I don't plan on attacking France early on, but if you do attack him, I would be happy to join. Or, if you would prefer to open to the east, that's fine too.
I can't early on, sorry. Would you be open to a central alliance?
Yes I would be!
I don't want to antagonize Austria early on. If you're worried about Burgundy you can support yourself in with Marseilles?
France told me he is interested in working with you.
But moving to Tyrolia is to attack Italy, not Austria?
That's good to hear. Do you know what he plans to do with his armies in the early game? Are they headed for me or for Italy?
I'm moving to Ruhr with Munich, to make sure I get Holland.
What if you move to Ruhr in the fall, we both just stay out of Burgundy.

Hi Turkey! I wanted to get in touch early on. Have you heard from Russia yet? I'd like it if he opens to the north so I can fight England. You don't have to attack him, of course. But it would be great if you could convince him to do so!
I'd be happy with that.
I do not know.
Will you open to the channel?
France just told me he is interested in working with you against England.
Have you heard from Italy?
Okay great. Have you heard from Italy yet?
He also told me he wants me to move Munich to Tyrolia, and I've told him that's not happening.
Interesting.
France is telling me he wants to work with me against England, so I think he might be willing to leave you alone early on.
Nope, no messages from him at all.
Neither Italy nor Turkey are responding to me, which means juggernaut is likely in play. I will likely need your help against Russia.
Have you heard from England?
Would you be up for moving Vienna to Tyrolia, so you can either use it against Italy if he isn't responding or help you against Russia, if he is?
Cool. I'll open channel, Pic, Spain, then build F Brest in the winter.
Austria says neither him or Turkey have heard from Russia either, so they might be planning a juggernaut.

messages.message: We can keep going like this forever... or you can go after England or Italy...
You can take Belgium if you want. BUR-BEL, HOL s BUR-BEL, NTH-NWY, SWE s NTH-NWY
The Med is open. Let's do a reverse Juggernaut...
KIE-RUH, MUN s KIE-RUH
And let Austria win?
No, he will take out Italy first... and if we stop fighting we can both slow him down.
How?
Yes, will do. Don't attack Munich though, or France will be able to get into Burgundy.
He already has 7 units
And Italy has only 4 sc
You build fleets.
I won't.
Italy has been a massive pain. I will consume him.
If I get back my sc
Good.
And you go for Russia?
Yes, but then you attack England, where we will have a chance at slowing Austria down...
Could you send a spare army to take STP next year?
No, I don't attack Russia. Russia will stop Austria from advancing north...
No deal
Also, if France dislodges you from BUR, don't retreat to MAR.
Maybe, depends on France.
